# ===== HOW TO GET THESE KEYS =====

# 1. Google OAuth:
#    - Go to: https://console.developers.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or select existing
#    - Enable Google+ API
#    - Go to Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client IDs
#    - Set authorized redirect URIs: http://localhost:3000, http://localhost:5173

# 2. Stripe:
#    - Go to: https://dashboard.stripe.com/
#    - Get your API keys from the Developers section
#    - Use test keys for development (they start with sk_test_ and pk_test_)

# 3. MongoDB:
#    - Use local MongoDB: mongodb://localhost:27017/quizbaaji
#    - Or MongoDB Atlas: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/quizbaaji

# 4. Email Service (Optional):
#    - Use Gmail app passwords or services like SendGrid, Mailgun

# ===== PRODUCTION NOTES =====
# 1. Change all "test" keys to "live" keys
# 2. Use strong JWT secret keys
# 3. Set proper CORS origins
# 4. Use environment variables in deployment
# 5. Enable HTTPS in production